I now understand both bugs. Let me trace through the code:

**Bug 1 (x-form-urlencoded)**: In `_extract_form_body`, when a Form field receives an empty string `""`, `_get_multidict_value` correctly returns the default (`None`). But then lines 905-907 blindly re-add all keys from the received body that aren't in `values`, overwriting the default with `""`.

**Bug 2 (multipart)**: Same root cause - the blind re-addition at lines 905-907.

The fix is to track processed keys (both field name and alias) and not re-add them. Let me implement this:
[0m
[0m← [0mEdit fastapi/dependencies/utils.py
Index: /private/var/folders/cf/sgp0bvks6t7br_0q2kj_5jpm0000gn/T/agentelo-AHakdi/fastapi/dependencies/utils.py
===================================================================
--- /private/var/folders/cf/sgp0bvks6t7br_0q2kj_5jpm0000gn/T/agentelo-AHakdi/fastapi/dependencies/utils.py
+++ /private/var/folders/cf/sgp0bvks6t7br_0q2kj_5jpm0000gn/T/agentelo-AHakdi/fastapi/dependencies/utils.py
@@ -870,8 +870,9 @@
     body_fields: List[ModelField],
     received_body: FormData,
 ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
     values = {}
+    processed_keys: set = set()
 
     for field in body_fields:
         value = _get_multidict_value(field, received_body)
         field_info = field.field_info
@@ -901,10 +902,12 @@
                     tg.start_soon(process_fn, sub_value.read)
             value = serialize_sequence_value(field=field, value=results)
         if value is not None:
             values[field.alias] = value
+        processed_keys.add(field.alias)
+        processed_keys.add(field.name)
     for key, value in received_body.items():
-        if key not in values:
+        if key not in processed_keys:
             values[key] = value
     return values
 
 

